The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 April is 312,093 (35,970.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 April, there were 198 new confirmed cases (22.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 April, there were 239 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 17% (41 fewer cases).
